nvironmental factors in complex diseases. Written by leading international experts and supplemented by a glossary and in-chapter guides to further reading, this essential textbook will be widely welcomed by teachers and students on many courses internationally.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aGenetic epidemiology. 0aMedical genetics. 7aMEDICAL / Epidemiology.2bisacsh1 aBarrett, Jennifer H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurton, Paul R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurton, Paul R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCardon, Lon R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClayton, David G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCordell, Heather J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavey Smith, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavey Smith, George, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDeschênes, Mylene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbrahim, Shah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFortier, Isabel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHansell, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHattersley, Andrew T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHopper, John L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewis, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCarthy, Mark I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalmer, Lyle J., 